[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two held in murder probe at Toddbury Farm travellers' site

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two people have been arrested on suspicion of murder following the death of a man in Bedfordshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police were called at 22:30 BST on Tuesday to a travellers' site at Toddbury Farm in Slapton Road, Little Billington, near Leighton Buzzard.
A man, aged 43, was taken to hospital where he was pronounced dead.
Police confirmed a man aged 24 and a woman, 42, have been arrested on suspicion of murder. Both remain in custody.
The victim, who officers say lived at the site, has not yet been named.
