Det Insp Alan Page from the Major Crime Unit said: "Though we appreciate the traumatic effect that an incident such as this will have on the traveller and wider community, we would urge members of the public not to be alarmed.
"We are conducting a full and thorough investigation into the events of last night and will maintain a visible, heightened presence in the area for reassurance and intelligence-gathering processes."
A post-mortem examination on the deceased man is expected to take place on Thursday.
